div.p: Genetic data from cancer cells predicts life expectancy.
Gene expression frequency determined from cancer cell molecular profile.
Genes vary greatly, from transmembrane proteins to gene-regulation segments Cancer patient survival status also tracked.

figure.figDesc: Gentles of Center for Cancer Systems Biology for data and support Cancer treatment is risky. Bone marrow transplants have a 30% death rate.Doctors must determine whether treatment truly increases chance of survival.
